org.trellisldp.api

Interface ResourceService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ImmutableDataService<Resource>, MutableDataService<Resource>, RetrievalService<Resource>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JoiningResourceService, TriplestoreResourceService

    public interface ResourceService
extends MutableDataService<Resource>, ImmutableDataService<Resource>
    The ResourceService provides methods for creating, retrieving and manipulating Trellis resources.

      • getContainer

        default Optional<IRI> getContainer(IRI identifier)
        Get the identifier for the structurally-logical container for the resource.

        Note: The returned identifier is not guaranteed to exist.

        Parameters:
        identifier - the identifier
        Returns:
        an identifier for the structurally-logical container

      • getMementos

        List<Range<Instant>> getMementos(IRI identifier)
        Retrieve a list of Mementos for this resource.
        Parameters:
        identifier - the resource identifier
        Returns:
        a List of Ranges of Instants. Each element of the list can be used to build a link header for a single Memento (i.e. for the from and until parameters)

      • compact

        Stream<IRI> compact(IRI identifier,
                    Instant from,
                    Instant until)
        Compact (rewrite the history) of a resource.
        Parameters:
        identifier - the identifier
        from - a time after which a resource is to be compacted
        until - a time before which a resource is to be compacted
        Returns:
        a stream of binary IRIs that can be safely purged
